## Deployment

{{#if (eq deployment "vercel")}}
### Vercel

```bash
# Install Vercel CLI
npm i -g vercel

# Deploy to preview
vercel

# Deploy to production
vercel --prod
```

Set environment variables in the [Vercel dashboard](https://vercel.com/dashboard) or with `vercel env add`.
{{/if}}

{{#if (eq deployment "fly")}}
### Fly.io

```bash
# Install flyctl
curl -L https://fly.io/install.sh | sh

# Create app (first time only)
fly launch

# Set secrets
fly secrets set DATABASE_URL="..." JWT_SECRET="..."

# Deploy
fly deploy
```
{{/if}}

{{#if (eq deployment "railway")}}
### Railway

1. Push your code to GitHub.
2. Create a new project at [railway.app](https://railway.app) and connect your repo.
3. Add environment variables in the Railway dashboard.
4. Railway will auto-deploy on every push to `main`.
{{/if}}

{{#if (eq deployment "docker")}}
### Docker

```bash
# Build the image
docker build -t {{projectName}} .

# Run with Docker Compose (includes database)
docker compose up -d

# View logs
docker compose logs -f
```

Edit `docker/docker-compose.yml` to configure services.
{{/if}}

{{#if (eq deployment "none")}}
### Self-Hosted

```bash
# Build
{{#if (eq packageManager "npm")}}npm run build{{/if}}
{{#if (eq packageManager "pnpm")}}pnpm build{{/if}}
{{#if (eq packageManager "yarn")}}yarn build{{/if}}
{{#if (eq packageManager "bun")}}bun run build{{/if}}

# Start production server
{{#if (eq packageManager "npm")}}npm start{{/if}}
{{#if (eq packageManager "pnpm")}}pnpm start{{/if}}
{{#if (eq packageManager "yarn")}}yarn start{{/if}}
{{#if (eq packageManager "bun")}}bun start{{/if}}
```
{{/if}}

